EJS Express JavaScript Templates
Used to render content on the server and send it to the user.

Items:
	-Views
	-Passing Data to a View
	-Partials
	-Layouts	
	-Using JS inside an EJS template.
	-Helpful Hints
		-html onerror tag
		-using CDNs to deliver CSS files	


Layout stuff:

	create a file under views called layouts/layout.ejs

	const expressLayouts = require('express-ejs-layouts');
	app.use(expressLayouts);
	app.set('view engine', 'ejs');
	app.set('layout', 'layout');

	res.render('about', { title: 'About Page', layout: './layouts/sidebar' })


Partials stuff

	Create a file partials/header.ejs and partials/footer.ejs

